class Solution {
    public boolean checkRecord(String s) {
        int countA = 0;
        int countL = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == 'A') {
                countA++;
                countL = 0;
            } else if (c == 'L') {
                countL++;
            } else {
                countL = 0;
            }
            if (countA >= 2 || countL >= 3) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once, maintaining counts of 'A' and consecutive 'L's. It immediately returns false when either condition is met, ensuring efficiency.
